@Plasmmer: Well, there is already basic Emoji-Support in probably most OS's 😄
And I actually think the EmojiOne-Emoji's are to pale for ZeroMe..

So maybe one of the "official" Devs for ZeroMe should decide, which they would like to use. :)

@Nofish: So I have to write that to every file in all users content.json-Files, or is there a way to define "globally", like in `data/users/content.json` or so?

E.g.:
```
  ...
  "permission_rules": {
   ".*": {
    "files_allowed": "data.json",
    "files_allowed_optional": ".+\\.(png|jpg|jpeg)",
    "max_size": 100000
   },
   ...
```
(I took [this one](http://127.0.0.1:43110/1MusicXkuN2pk5hRdmroeyaCLDJtzTicpB/data/users/content.json) as template)

@Plasmmer: :?
It isn't a Hub, or is it x?

PS.: I believe I removed that `"merged_type": "ZeroMe"`-Property from content.json for now, though I thought that's how I get the data from ZeroMe!?!

@Sirenyc: Thanks :)

To upload a media-file, you either need to click the "plus"-icon to the left of the message-input, then select your file, and click the now "upload"-icon, or you go to the "Media"-Tab at the top, select your file, and click the "upload"-icon.

If you still experience any errors, you might want to send me the consoles log :)
